documentation.text:
@dev Delegates voting power of this contract to another address.
 @param _delegate: address - Address of delegate.

@dev Retrieves current state of the proposal  
 @return ProposalState - The state of the proposal
    Pending: 0
    Active: 1
    Canceled: 2
    Defeated: 3 
    Succeeded: 4
    Queued: 5
    Expired: 6
    Executed: 7

VoteDelegated(address).details: Emitted when a user delegates voting power.

constructor.details: Constructor for the VoteProxyERC20 contract    - Immediately self delegates voting power     - Sets owner of the contract to the user   - Sets proxy factory as msg.sender  TODO:    1. The treasury token address will be a fixed address    2. Token pool will be fixed address

params._governanceToken: : address - The address of the governance token
params._governor: : address - The address of the governor contract for the DAO
params._tokenPool: : address - The address of the token pool contract that the token came from
params._user: : address - Address of the end user

deFundMe().details: (for now you can only fully defund) - Avoids conversion from GT --> TSRY     - Sends back all GT to token pool.     - Sends back TSRY to user

delegateVotingRights(address).details: Delegates voting power of this contract to another address.

fundMe(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Stakes treasury and makes an external call to the voteproxyfactory in order to fund this contract with the corresponding amount of governance token

params._stakeAmount: : uint - Amount user has to deposit into this contract
params._tsryPrice: : uint - for testing, the price of tsry.

getState(uint256).details: Retrieves current state of the proposal

returns._0: ProposalState - The state of the proposal    Pending: 0    Active: 1    Canceled: 2    Defeated: 3     Succeeded: 4    Queued: 5    Expired: 6    Executed: 7

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxyVote(uint8,uint256).details: Vote with amount of governance token stored in contract.     - Sends TSRY back to the user.    - Sends back all GT to token pool.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
